p.gr/eng/station.asp?id=13|archivedate=22 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{coord|38|00|43|N|23|43|43|E|type:railwaystation_source:kolossus-frwiki|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Athens Metro stations]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1956]]\n\n\n{{Greece-railstation-stub}}\n{{Athens-struct-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ymblanter", "label": "safe", "comment": "+ short description", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kato_Patisia_metro_station"}
{"title_page": "1983 NatWest Trophy", "text_new": "{{use dmy dates|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox cricket tournament\n| image = \n| imagesize = \n| caption = \n| administrator = [[Test and County Cricket Board]]\n| cricket format = [[Limited overs cricket]]{{Clear}}(60 overs per innings)\n| tournament format = [[Single-elimination tournament|Knockout]]\n| champions = [[Somerset County Cricket Club|Somerset]]\n| count = 2\n| participants = 32\n| matches = 30\n| most runs = '''279''' [[Chris Tavar\u00e9]] (Kent)\n| most wickets =  '''14''' [[Joel Garner]] (Somerset) \n| website = [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Seasons/ENG/1983_ENG_National_Westminster_Bank_Trophy_1983.html CricketArchive tournament page]\n| previous_year = 1982\n| previous_tournament = 1982 NatWest Trophy\n| next_year = 1984\n| next_tournament = 1984 NatWest Trophy\n}}\n\nThe '''1983 NatWest Trophy''' was the 3rd [[Friends Provident Trophy|NatWest Trophy]].  It was an English [[limited overs cricket|limited overs]] [[county cricket]] tournament which was held between 29 June and 3 September 1983.<ref>{{cite web |url-access=subscription |url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Seasons/ENG/1983_ENG_National_Westminster_Bank_Trophy_1983.html|title=NatWest Trophy, 1983 - Fixtures|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=22 May 2010}}</ref>  The tournament was won by [[Somerset County Cricket Club]] who defeated [[Kent County Cricket Club]] by 24 runs in the final at [[Lord's]].\n\n==Format==\nThe seventeen [[first-class cricket|first-class]] counties, were joined by thirteen [[Minor counties of English cricket|Minor Counties]].  This was a change from the previous versions of the competition, where only five Minor Counties were permitted to take part. The Minor Counties taking part were: [[Berkshire County Cricket Club|Berkshire]], [[Cambridgeshire County Cricket Club|Cambridgeshire]], [[Cheshire County Cricket Club|Cheshire]], [[Devon County Cricket Club|Devon]], [[Dorset County Cricket Club|Dorset]], [[Durham County Cricket Club|Durham]], [[Hertfordshire County Cricket Club|Hertfordshire]], [[Lincolnshire County Cricket Club|Lincolnshire]], [[Norfolk County Cricket Club|Norfolk]], [[Oxfordshire County Cricket Club|Oxfordshire]], [[Shropshire County Cricket Club|Shropshire]], [[Suffolk County Cricket Club|Suffolk]] and [[Wiltshire County Cricket Club|Wiltshire]].  The [[Ireland national cricket team]] also participated, along with for the first time the [[Scotland national cricket team]].  Teams who won in the first round progressed to the second round. The winners in the second round then progressed to the quarter-final stage.  Winners from the quarter-finals then progressed to the semi-finals from which the winners then went on to the final at [[Lord's]] which was held on 3 September 1983.\n\n===First round===\n{{Limited Overs Matches\n | date = 29 June 1983\n | team1 = [[Berkshire County Cricket Club|Berkshire]]\n | score1 = 128/9 (60 overs)\n | score2 = 131/3 (50.4 overs)\n | team2 = [[Yorkshire County Cricket Club|Yorkshire]]\n | runs1 = [[Graham Roope]] 29\n | wickets1 = [[Graham Stevenson]] 5/27 (12 overs)\n | runs2 = [[Geoffrey Boycott]] 48\n | wickets2 = [[Martin Lickley]] 1/15 (5 overs)\n | result = Yorkshire won by 3 wickets\n | report = [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/43/43698.html (scorecard)]\n | venue = [[Church Road Cricket Ground|Church Road]], [[Reading, Berkshire|Reading]]\n | umpires = [[Ray Julian]] & [[Peter Stevens (umpire)|Peter Stevens]]\n | motm = [[Graham Stevenson]] (Yorkshire)\n | rain = \n}}\n----\n{{Limited Overs Matches\n | date = 29 June 1983\n | team1 = [[Cambridgeshire County Cricket Club|Cambridgeshire]]\n | score1 = 172 all out (58.4 overs)\n | score2 = 174/2 (51 overs)\n | team2 = [[Middlesex County Cricket Club|Middlesex]]\n | runs1 = [[Nigel Gadsby]] 63\n | wickets1 = [[John Emburey]] 2/27 (12 overs)\n | runs2 = [[Keith Tomlins]] 80\n | wickets2 = [[Gary Rice]] 1/31 (12 overs)\n | result = Middlesex won by 8 wi