Explaining Loyalty and Defection of Militant Organizations toward Pakistan |journal=Studies in Conflict & Terrorism |volume=38 |number=11 |year=2015 |pp=919\u2013937 |DOI=10.1080/1057610X.2015.1063838 |ref={{sfnref|Popovic, The Perils of Weak Organization|2015}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Moj |first=Muhammad |title=The Deoband Madrassah Movement: Countercultural Trends and Tendencies |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mbm2BgAAQBAJ&pg=PA98 |year=2015 |publisher=Anthem Press |ISBN=978-1-78308-389-3 |ref={{sfnref|Moj, Deoband Madrassah Movement|2015}}}}\n* {{cite web |title=Foreign Islamic Jihadis Organizations (FTOs) |url=https://2001-2009.state.gov/s/ct/rls/fs/37191.htm |publisher=[[United States Department of State]] |date=11 October 2005}}\n* {{cite web |last=Moore |first=John |title=The Evolution of Islamic Terrorism: An Overview |work=Frontline: Target America |publisher=PBS Online and WGBH/Frontline |year=2001 |url=https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/shows/target/etc/modern.html |accessdate=2009-12-02}}\n* {{citation |last=[[Ahmed Rashid|Rashid]] |first=Ahmed |title=Descent into Chaos: How the War Against Islamic Extremism is Being Lost in Pakistan, Afghanistan and Central Asia |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lMUE2SuQ-eMC |date=2012 |publisher=Penguin Books Limited |ISBN=978-0-14-191909-6 |ref={{sfnref|Rashid, Descent into Chaos|2012}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Riedel |first=Bruce O. |title=Deadly Embrace: Pakistan, America, and the Future of the Global Jihad |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ULgk7_oWB1EC |date=2012 |publisher=Brookings Institution Press |isbn=0-8157-2274-5 |ref={{sfnref|Riedel, Deadly Embrace|2012}}}}\n\n\n{{War on Terrorism|state=collapsed}}\n{{Kashmir separatist movement}}\n{{Terror outfits in India}}\n\n[[Category:2000 establishments in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Jihadist groups in Jammu and Kashmir]]\n[[Category:Groups affiliated with al-Qaeda]]\n[[Category:Organizations designated as terrorist by Canada]]\n", "name_user": "2409:404