rd|38|03|57|N|23|48|14|E|display=title}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name            =\n{{Infobox station/Header OASA\n|native_name=\u039a\u0391\u03a4\n|name       =KAT\n|mode       =M\n|mode_2     =\n|line_1     =M1\n|line_2     =\n}}\n| type            = \n| style           = \n| image           = Kat-stathmos.jpg\n| image_size      =\n| image_caption   = \n| address         = \n| country         =\n| coordinates     = \n| elevation       = \n| line            = {{OASA icons|M1}}\n| other           = \n| structure       = \n| platform        = 2\n| depth           = \n| levels          = \n| tracks          = 2\n| parking         = \n| bicycle         = \n| opened          = 27 March 1989\n| closed          = \n| rebuilt         = \n| electrified     = \n| ADA             = yes\n| code            = \n| owned           = \n| operator        = [[Athens Metro]]\n| zone            = \n| smartcardname   =\n| smartcardstatus = \n| former          = \n| passengers      = \n| pass_year       = \n| pass_percent    = \n| pass_system     = \n| mpassengers     = \n| services        = \n{{s-rail|title=OASA Metro}}\n{{s-line|system=OASA Metro|line=M1|previous=Marousi|next=Kifisia}}\n| map_locator     = \n| route_map       = \n| map_state       = \n}}\n\n'''KAT station''' ({{lang-el|\u03a3\u03c4\u03b1\u03b8\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2 \u039a\u0391\u03a4 or Stathmos KAT}}) is an [[Athens Metro]] train station in [[Kifissia]], [[Greece]], next to the [[KAT Hospital|Traumatic Recovery Center]] (KAT), from which it derives its name. The station is situated several kilometres north of [[Athens]] and 24.631&nbsp;km from the starting point in [[Piraeus station|Piraeus]]. The station was opened on March 27, 1989, and was renovated in 2004. It contains two platforms.\n\n[[Category:Athens Metro stations]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1989]]\n\n{{Greece-railstation-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ymblanter", "label": "safe", "comment": "+ short description", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KAT_metro_station"}
